---
import Layout from '../../Base.astro';
import SimpleHero from '../../components/SimpleHero.astro';
import FeaturedArticles from '../../components/FeaturedArticles.astro';
import ServicesRelatedWork from '../../components/ServicesRelatedWork.astro';
import '../../styles/pages/_services-list.scss';
---

<Layout
  title="Custom Applications | Florida Software Agency"
  description="We design and build custom web applications that streamline operations, connect systems, and give your business more control over how it works and scales."
>
  <SimpleHero
    tagline="Custom Application Development"
    title="Applications Built Around Your Business"
    description="When your business outgrows off-the-shelf tools, custom applications give you the control to streamline operations, connect systems, and build exactly what you need—without compromise."
    lottieFile="content-creation.json"
  />

  <div class="service-body">
    <div class="wrapper wrapper--narrow">
      <h2>When custom applications make sense</h2>
      <p>
        Most businesses start with existing tools. Over time, those tools become limiting—forcing workarounds,
        duplicating effort, or creating gaps between systems that should be connected.
      </p>
      <p>
        Custom applications solve those problems by aligning software directly with how your business operates. Instead
        of adapting your workflow to a platform, the platform is built around your workflow.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Internal tools that replace manual or repetitive processes</li>
        <li>Dashboards that surface real-time business data</li>
        <li>Systems that connect multiple platforms into a single workflow</li>
        <li>Customer-facing tools that improve experience and accessibility</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What we actually build</h2>
      <p>
        Every application is different, but the goal is consistent: create a system that is reliable, maintainable, and
        built to scale with your business.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Custom web applications</li>
        <li>Internal dashboards and admin tools</li>
        <li>API integrations and system connections</li>
        <li>Data visualization and reporting interfaces</li>
        <li>Performance-focused, device-agnostic builds</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we approach it</h2>
      <p>
        We don’t start with technology—we start with structure. Understanding how your business operates determines what
        should be built, how it should function, and what success looks like.
      </p>

      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Define the system:</strong> Identify gaps, inefficiencies, and opportunities in your current workflow.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Map the structure:</strong> Outline how data, users, and actions should interact.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Design the interface:</strong> Create clear, usable experiences based on real use cases—not assumptions.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Build and integrate:</strong> Develop the application and connect it to the systems you already use.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Refine and scale:</strong> Improve performance, expand functionality, and support long-term growth.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2>The outcome</h2>
      <p>
        A well-built application reduces friction inside your business. It saves time, eliminates duplication, and gives
        your team better visibility into what matters.
      </p>
      <p>
        More importantly, it creates a foundation you can build on—rather than a system you eventually have to replace.
      </p>

      <p>
        <a href="/contact/" class="button button--green">Start a Project</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <ServicesRelatedWork tag={75} />
  </div>

  <FeaturedArticles />
</Layout>
